{
  "texts": [
    "To proceed, we introduce a perturbed problem with perturbation M ν:P ⋆ (ν):= maximize π ∈ Π E x E y ∼ π(• | x) [ r(x, y) -βE x [ D KL (π(• | x) ∥ π ref (• | x))] subject to E x E y ∼ π(• | x) [ h i (x, y)] ≥ M ν, for all i = 1,..., m.We denote its solution by π ⋆ ν.",
    "By Assumption 4, strong duality holds:P ⋆ (ν) = minimize λ ≥ 0 maximize π ∈ Π L ν (π, λ):= L(π, λ) -M ν ∥λ∥ 1where L ν (π, λ) is the perturbed Lagrangian, and we denote the minimizer above by λ ⋆ ν.From the definition of D p (λ), haveD ⋆ p ≤ D p (λ):= maximize θ ∈ Θ L(π θ, λ) for any λ ≥ 0 which implies that D ⋆ p ≤ maximize θ ∈ Θ L(π θ, λ ⋆ ν) ≤ maximize π ∈ Π L(π, λ ⋆ ν) = maximize π ∈ Π L ν (π, λ ⋆ ν) + M ν ∥λ ⋆ ν ∥ 1where the second inequality is due to that π θ ∈ Π. Hence,D ⋆ p ≤ E x E y ∼ π ⋆ ν (• | x) [ r(x, y) -βE x [ D KL (π ⋆ ν (• | x) ∥ π ref (• | x))] + M ν ∥λ ⋆ ν ∥ 1.On the other hand, by Assumption 3, there exists a policy π ⋆ p (λ ⋆ ν) such thatE x E y ∼ π ⋆ p (• | x;λ ⋆ ν) [ h i (x, y)] -E x E y ∼ π ⋆ ν (• | x) [ h i (x, y)] ≤ M ν which implies that π ⋆ p (λ ⋆ ν) is feasible for Problem (P-CA).",
    "Thus, D ⋆ p ≤ P ⋆ p + E x E y ∼ π ⋆ ν (• | x) [ r(x, y) -βE x [ D KL (π ⋆ ν (• | x) ∥ π ref (• | x))] -P ⋆ p + M ν ∥λ ⋆ ν ∥ 1 ≤ P ⋆ p + E x E y ∼ π ⋆ p (• | x;λ ⋆ ν) [ r(x, y)] -E x E y ∼ π ⋆ ν (• | x) [ r(x, y)] + β E x [ D KL (π ⋆ ν (• | x) ∥ π ref (• | x))] -E x D KL (π ⋆ p (• | x; λ ⋆ ν) ∥ π ref (• | x)) + M ν ∥λ ⋆ ν ∥ 1 ≤ P ⋆ p + M ν 1 + βν KL + M ν ∥λ ⋆ ν ∥ 1where the second inequality is due to the suboptimal π ⋆ p (λ ⋆ ν):P ⋆ p ≥ E x E y ∼ π ⋆ p (• | x;λ ⋆ ν) [ r(x, y)] -βE x D KL (π ⋆ p (• | x; λ ⋆ ν) ∥ π ref (• | x))and the last inequality is due to Assumption 3.",
    "B.3 Proof of Lemma 3Proof.",
    "By Assumption 3, for any π ⋆ (λ), there exists a θ ∈ Θ such that ∥πθ(• | x) -π ⋆ (• | x; λ)∥ 1 ≤ ν 1 and |D KL (π ⋆ (• | x; λ) ∥ π ref (• | x)) -D KL (πθ(• | x) ∥ π ref (• | x))| ≤ ν KL."
  ]
